metadata.name: Stereo Print #44
metadata.description:
Generative audio painted on canvas. Tap to see and hear the composition in real time.

Stereo Print is my second collection in the paint-with-sound genre. Each mint has uniquely generated two-channel audio in the style of jazz, distortion, chimes, tones, space, or noise. The piece's visual texture is sourced directly from the audio signal. The raw waveforms are layered, masked, and transformed to produce the final composition.

Made with Web Audio and p5js. Idlebit, 2022.

metadata.name: Sea of Shapes #12
metadata.description:
This program was inspired by the 2022 Genuary prompt "Make a sea of shapes." It is an abstract and geometric representation of water and waves. I tried to capture the many different possible states of a sea (windy, breezy, calm etc.) by changing parameters within the program for different outputs.

Press 'p' while on Live View to save a high quality (4000x4000) png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

Licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Ornithic #152
metadata.description:
Pure p5.js code. No svg, no image, no other materials. Creating code arts with polar coordinate system and algorithms are my passion. This generative art contains a lot of features that may be rare than common.  

• 30 color palettes // 2 of them have 3 different colors
• 4 grass structures // With the same algorithm 
• 16 flower types //  Count, leaf number and size
• 6 color functions // Different colorizations with b&w 

Also, the outputs of the project are very high resolution to print or something like that.
April / 2022
Rhaegar

metadata.name: Giza #31
metadata.description:
Tried to catch a poetic atmosphere working on this generative representation of the pyramids of Giza.
Built by thousands of humans during tens of years thousands years ago they're now generated in seconds with millions of dots by a javascript algorithm.
That's were knowledge has led us !

Features
 - Time: Day (probability 1/2) / Night (probability 1/2)
 - Mode: Dark (probability 5/6) / Light (probability 1/6)
 - Number of pyramids
 - Background dunes
 - Global ligthness
 - Sun/Moon shine
 - generative color palette

Only Javascript / No library used

metadata.name: Refractions #164
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Organicon, variation II #84
metadata.description:
Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
One of 128 unique generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation II is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. A small counter in the lower-right corner displays the progress.

Interface: on first load the piece operates in active mode. In this mode an iteration is cleared 30s after completion and replaced by the next iteration. This mode is indicated by a flashing dot in the upper-right corner.

A first mouse click disables active mode. The current iteration will complete and remain on screen. A second mouse click clears the screen, loads the next iteration, and reenables active mode.
